Summary: Brief sighting as it flew overhead.
divs: sighting detailsrelaxing on the deck and watching the sky. around 8:28 p.m i noticed a light moving over my head, sw to ne. i first thought it was the iss so i checked the heavens above web site. it was not the iss. on saturday evening 8\3\13 at around 21:56 me and some friends watched the iss fly over at a magnitude -3.5. the sky was dark. tonight the sky was still a bit light and i'd guesstimate the magnitude to be around -1.5 to -2.0. i was able to observe the light for about 20 seconds until it disappeared into some light cloud cover. the object was star-like, no blinking and no nav lights and appeared to be traveling a little faster than the iss normally travels. my observation position is: pioneer ca, 38.4300���n, 120.5747���w
